entries.npc_11: Be seein' ya.  You won't see me, but I'll be seeing you.
entries.npc_5: The Imperials send their commandos, their soldiers, their droids.  None of them find me.  Except the ones that are already dead.
entries.npc_9: There's nothing anyone can do to stop me.  And there is no answer to that question.
entries.npc_8: Things are always weird here in the Jungle.  The Imperials want me dead and the Jungle keeps me alive.  That's the way it is.
entries.npc_4: You know what you call an assassin who goes out to kill another assassin?
entries.npc_3: Of course.  There always are.  Errand boys mostly, sent down to collect the bill for a check they don't deserve.
entries.npc_7: I have to be to survive out here?  You don't know what it takes to survive in this jungle.
entries.npc_6: You'd better.  You have no idea the horrors I've seen.
entries.npc_2: Good.  Cause it wasn't going to happen if you were.
entries.player_2: Are there people trying to kill you?
entries.npc_1: You're not here to kill me are you?
